quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,"Does he not know, when that which is in the graves is scattered abroad"
  100,10,And that which is in the chest is made manifest
  100,11,That their Guardian Evolver had been well acquainted with them that day
  101,1,The Disaster
  101,2,What is the Disaster
  101,3,And what will explain to you what the Disaster is
  101,4,It is a day when humanity will be like scattered moths
  101,5,And the mountains will be as wool
  101,6,Then he whose scales will be heavy
  101,7,Will be in a life of blessings and satisfaction
  101,8,But he whose scale will be found light
  101,9,Will have his home in a pit
  101,10,And what will explain to you what this is
  101,11,It is a fire blazing fiercely
  102,1,The competition for accumulating diverts you
  102,2,Until you all visit the graves
  102,3,"But no, you will soon know"
  102,4,"Again, you will soon know"
  102,5,"No, were you to know with certainty of mind"
  102,6,You will certainly see hellfire
  102,7,"Again, you will see it with certainty of sight"
  102,8,"Then, you will be questioned that day about the pleasure you indulged in"
  103,1,By time
  103,2,Indeed the human being is lost
  103,3,"Except those who have faith, work to make things right, and join together in the mutual teaching of truth, patience, and constancy"
  104,1,"Woe to every scandalous, backbiter"
  104,2,Who accumulates wealth and counts it
  104,3,Thinking that his wealth will make him last forever
  104,4,By no means. He will surely be thrown into that which breaks into pieces
  104,5,And what will explain to you about that which breaks into pieces
  104,6,It is the fire of God kindled to a blaze
  104,7,That mounts right up to the hearts
  104,8,It will be made into a vault over them
  104,9,"In columns, extended"
  105,1,Do you not see how your Lord dealt with the companions of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their treacherous plan go astray
  105,3,And He sent against them flocks of birds
  105,4,Striking them with stones of baked clay
  105,5,Then He made them like an empty field of stalks and straw which has been eaten
  106,1,For the security enjoyed by the Quraysh
  106,2,Their security covering journeys by winter and summer
  106,3,Let them adore the Guardian Evolver of this house
  106,4,"Who provides them with food against hunger, and with security against fear of danger"
  107,1,Do you see the one who denies the Judgment
  107,2,They are those who repulse the orphan
  107,3,And do not encourage the feeding of the indigent
  107,4,So woe to the worshippers
  107,5,Who are neglectful of their prayers
  107,6,Those who want to be seen
  107,7,But refuse to do even neighborly deeds
  108,1,"To you, We have granted the fountain of abundance"
  108,2,Therefore turn in prayer and sacrifice to your Lord
  108,3,"For he who hates you, he will be cut off"
  109,1,"Say, O you who do not believe"
  109,2,I do not worship that which you worship
  109,3,Nor will you worship that which I worship
  109,4,And I will not worship that which you are accustomed to worshiping
  109,5,Nor will you worship that which I worship
  109,6,"To you your way, and to me, my way"
  110,1,When the help of God and victory comes
  110,2,And you see the people enter God's religion in crowds
  110,3,"Glorify by Praising your Guardian Evolver, and pray for His forgiveness, for He is Oft-Forgiving"
  111,1,"May the hands of the father of the flame perish, and may he perish"
  111,2,"No profit will he have for all his wealth, and all his gains"
  111,3,He will soon burn in a fire of a blazing flame
  111,4,His wife will carry the wood as fuel
  111,5,With a twisted rope of palm-leaf fiber around her neck
  112,1,"Say, He is God, the One and Only"
  112,2,"God, the Eternal, Absolute"
  112,3,"He has no children, nor was He born"
  112,4,And nothing is like Him
  113,1,"Say, I seek refuge with the Guardian Evolver of the dawn"
  113,2,From the harm of created things
  113,3,From the harm of darkness as it overspreads
  113,4,From the harm of those who whisper into convictions
  113,5,And from the harm of the envious one as he practices envy
  114,1,"Say, I seek refuge with the Guardian Evolver of humanity"
  114,2,The King of humanity
  114,3,The God of humanity
  114,4,"From the harm of the whisperer, who withdraws after he whispers"
  114,5,And who whispers into the hearts of humanity
  114,6,Among jinn and humanity